# MDF-7 fixture: cvs/.rsync-filter
# Exercises: dir-merge `:C` (CVS bundle). When `C` is present, upstream
# bundles FILTRULE_NO_PREFIXES | FILTRULE_WORD_SPLIT | FILTRULE_NO_INHERIT
# | FILTRULE_CVS_IGNORE and defaults the merge filename to `.cvsignore`.
# Tracking: filter-rules-status.md section 3.1 (MDF-2 fix scope).
# Upstream reference: exclude.c:1248-1255.

# CVS-style dir-merge: defaults to reading .cvsignore in each dir and
# bundles the upstream `default_cvsignore` set (CVS/, RCS, SCCS,
# `.svn/`, `.git/`, `.hg/`, `.bzr/`, `*.o`, `*~`, etc).
#
# Note: the sibling `dot-git/` directory in this fixture is renamed to
# `.git/` by materialize.sh before the transfer runs, because git
# cannot track a nested `.git/` directory.
:C
